#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advanced Usage"
msgstr "Utilisation avancée"

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Options"
msgstr "Options en ligne de commande"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:7
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "When running &appname; from the command line, there are several options "
#| "for opening data files. They may be seen by running <userinput>tellico --"
#| "help</userinput>."
msgid ""
"When running &appname; from the command line, there are several options for "
"opening data files. They may be seen by running <userinput>tellico --help</"
"userinput>. Diagnostic logging can also be enabled, which will make a <link "
"linkend=\"settings-help-menu\">menu item</link> to show the diagnostic log. "
"The <userinput>--logfile</userinput> option redirects the log to a file."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque vous lancez &appname; depuis la ligne de commande, plusieurs options "
"existent pour ouvrir des fichiers de données. Elles peuvent être affichées "
"en écrivant <userinput>tellico --help</userinput>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: advanced.docbook:11
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Usage: tellico [Qt-options] [KDE-options] [options] [filename]\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Tellico - a collection manager for KDE\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Options:\n"
#| "  --nofile                  Do not reopen the last open file\n"
#| "  --bibtex                  Import &lt;filename&gt; as a bibtex file\n"
#| "  --mods                    Import &lt;filename&gt; as a MODS file\n"
#| "  --ris                     Import &lt;filename&gt; as a RIS file\n"
#| "\n"
#| "Arguments:\n"
#| "  filename                  File to open"
msgid ""
"Usage: tellico [options] [filename]\n"
"\n"
"Tellico - collection management software, free and simple\n"
"\n"
"Options:\n"
"  --nofile                  Do not reopen the last open file\n"
"  --bibtex                  Import &lt;filename&gt; as a bibtex file\n"
"  --mods                    Import &lt;filename&gt; as a MODS file\n"
"  --ris                     Import &lt;filename&gt; as a RIS file\n"
"  --pdf                     Import &lt;filename&gt; as a PDF file\n"
"  --log                     Log diagnostic output\n"
"  --logfile &lt;logfile&gt;       Write log output to &lt;filename&gt;\n"
"\n"
"Arguments:\n"
"  [filename]                File to open"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : tellico [options-Qt] [options-KDE] [options] [filename]\n"
"\n"
"Tellico - un gestionnaire de collections pour KDE\n"
"\n"
"Options : \n"
"  --nofile                  Ne pas charger le dernier fichier ouvert\n"
"  --bibtex                  Importer le &lt;filename&gt; en tant que fichier "
"bibtex\n"
"  --mods                    Importer le &lt;filename&gt; en tant que fichier "
"MODS\n"
"  --ris                     Importer le &lt;filename&gt; en tant que fichier "
"RIS\n"
"\n"
"Arguments : \n"
"  filename                  Fichier à ouvrir"

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "&DBus; Interface"
msgstr "L'interface &DBus;"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; has a minimal &DBus; interface, which can be useful for scripting "
"or interacting with a running application from the command-line. As with all "
"&DBus; calls, you need to specify the service you want to interface with, "
"and the particular interface. The name of the &DBus; service is "
"<constant>org.kde.tellico</constant>."
msgstr ""
"&appname; a une interface &DBus; minimale permettant de scripter ou "
"d'interagir avec des applications lancées depuis la ligne de commande. Comme "
"pour tous les appels &DBus;, vous devrez spécifier le service à contrôler "
"ainsi que son interface. Le nom du service &DBus; est <constant>org.kde."
"tellico</constant>."

#. Tag: title
#: advanced.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "&DBus; Commands"
msgstr "Les commandes &DBus;"

#. Tag: para
#: advanced.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two &DBus; primary objects are available in the tellico interface: "
"<constant>Tellico</constant> and <constant>Collections</constant>."
msgstr ""
"Deux objets &DBus; sont accessibles par l'interface de Tellico : "
"<constant>Tellico</constant> et <constant>Collections</constant>."

